message.content: We set up a proportion to solve for the distance Jana will walk in 10 minutes. Because 24 minutes corresponds to one mile, then $\frac{1}{24}$ of a mile correspond to a minute walk. Therefore, if $x$ is the distance Jana walks in 10 minutes, then $\frac{1}{24}=\frac{x}{10}$. Cross-multiplying gives $240=24x$, so $x=\boxed{10}$.
